BD BOARD DECLARES DIVIDEND
 
Franklin Lakes, NJ (November 20, 2007)
 The Board of Directors of BD (Becton, Dickinson and Company) (NYSE:BDX) has declared a quarterly dividend of 28.5 cents per common share, an increase of 4 cents per share, or 16.3%, from the previous quarter. The dividend will be payable on January 2, 2008 to holders of record on December 12, 2007. At the current rate, the annual dividend for fiscal 2008 would be $1.14 per share.
 
"This marks the 35 consecutive year that BD has increased its dividend. We are committed to a very strong return of cash to our shareholders," said Edward J. Ludwig, BD Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer.
